Bluetongue [BTV], Croatia
-------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 18 Jan 2016 from Dr Mirjana Matausic-Pisl, assistant to minister, Ministry of Agriculture, Veterinary Directorate, Ministry of Agriculture, Zagreb, Croatia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 15 Dec 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 15 Jan 2016
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: December 2015
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: bluetongue virus
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Viljevo, Viljevo, Viljevo, [Osijek-Baranja]
Date of start of the outbreak: 15 Dec 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 37 / 1 / - / - / -
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 3 / ** / **/ **
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors

Control measures
Measures applied: screening; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; control of vectors; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Croatian Veterinary Institute, Split (national laboratory) / Cattle / competitive ELISA (c-ELISA) / 24 Dec 2015 / Positive
Croatian Veterinary Institute, Split (national laboratory) / Cattle / reverse transcription - polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 15 Jan 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of this outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

